member.param:
A value indicating whether to reset cached values if the current source is different from the previously
            cached source. If , the cache is cleared and updated if the source has changed;
            otherwise, the cache remains unchanged.

member.summary:
A themed, drop-in replacement for . It mirrors the full set of Show overloads and reuses the standard WPF dialog enums (, , and ) so that existing code can switch to it with a single using alias:
using MessageBox = Mosaic.UI.Wpf.Controls.MessageBox;
The dialog honors the active Mosaic light/dark/high-contrast theme.

member.returns:
The RelativePanel.AlignBottomWithPanel XAML attached property value of the specified
   object. (true to align this element's bottom edge with the panel's bottom edge;
otherwise, false.)

The RelativePanel.AlignHorizontalCenterWithPanel XAML attached property value
of the specified object. (true to horizontally center this element in the panel;
otherwise, false.)

The RelativePanel.AlignRightWithPanel XAML attached property value of the specified
object. (true to align this element's right edge with the panel's right edge;
otherwise, false.)

member.summary:
Gets or sets the orientation of the split. 
(the default) stacks the panes top/bottom with a horizontal splitter; 
places the panes side-by-side with a vertical splitter.

Gets or sets the maximum number of scrolled-off lines retained for scrollback.
Set to 0 to disable scrollback. Defaults to 1000. Only the main screen has scrollback;
the alternate screen buffer never contributes history.

